OL,3,CMPs to debate social media ban for
OL,4,Cunder-16s after support for petition
OL,6,FIt argues that a ban would help stop
OL,7,Fonline bullying, stop children being
OL,8,Finfluenced by false posts and stop
OL,9,Fchildren seeing content that
OL,10,Fencourages violence, or could be
OL,11,Fharmful for their future.
OL,13,FThe discussion comes after Australia's
OL,14,Fgovernment voted to ban social media
OL,15,Ffor under 16s last November, although
OL,16,Fthe legislation may not take effect
OL,17,Funtil later this year. That ban could
OL,18,Fsee tech companies fined millions if
OL,19,Fthey don't comply.
