OL,3,CMPs to debate social media ban for
OL,4,Cunder-16s after support for petition
OL,6,FThe protection of children is one of
OL,7,Fthe key aims of the Online Safety Act
OL,8,F2023. Under the act, social media
OL,9,Fcompanies must protect children in a
OL,10,Fnumber of ways including by removing
OL,11,Fillegal content quickly or preventing
OL,12,Fit from appearing in the first place.
OL,14,FIt must also prevent children from
OL,15,Faccessing harmful content, and use age-
OL,16,Fchecking measures so that children
OL,17,Fcannot access pornographic material
OL,18,Fand other age-inappropriate content.
OL,19,FThe regulator, Ofcom, is implementing
OL,20,Fthe act in phases and the new
OL,21,Flegislation is yet to be tested.
